# ============================================================================
# SPRING SPARROW FINANCIAL ADVISOR (SSFAP)
# ============================================================================
# 
# File: .gitignore
# Version: 1.0.0
# Last Updated: 2026-02-14
# 
# PURPOSE:
# Tells Git which files to never commit to GitHub. Critical for security
# (prevents exposing Firebase keys, API secrets) and cleanliness (no build
# artifacts, dependency folders).
# 
# BUSINESS CONTEXT:
# This app handles sensitive financial data. Firebase credentials, if exposed,
# could allow unauthorized access to your business data. .env files contain
# these credentials and must NEVER be committed.
# 
# ============================================================================

# Logs
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

# Dependencies
node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?

# ============================================================================
# FIREBASE SECURITY (CRITICAL - DO NOT REMOVE)
# ============================================================================

# Environment variables containing Firebase credentials
# NEVER commit these files - they contain API keys and project IDs
.env
.env.local
.env.production
.env.development
.env.*.local

# Firebase cache and config
.firebase/
.firebaserc
firebase-debug.log
firebase-debug.*.log

# ============================================================================
# BUILD ARTIFACTS
# ============================================================================

# Vite build output
dist/
build/

# Test coverage
coverage/

# ============================================================================
# OPERATING SYSTEM FILES
# ============================================================================

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db

# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# ============================================================================
# WHAT'S INCLUDED IN GIT (NOT IGNORED)
# ============================================================================
# 
# These files ARE committed:
# - Source code (src/)
# - Package configs (package.json, vite.config.js)
# - README and documentation
# - Public assets
# 
# These files are NEVER committed:
# - .env files (contain secrets)
# - node_modules (can reinstall with npm install)
# - Build output (generated from source)
# - Editor settings (personal preferences)
# 
# ============================================================================